h%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Someone%20enjoys%20increasingly%20spicy%20food.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655cd58f4ca513d8242cd4c1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EChelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFrom%20extreme%20hot%20sauces%20to%20online%20spice%20challenges%2C%20Americans%20have%20long%20had%20a%20fascination%20with%20spice.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChile%20pepper%20production%20has%20consistently%20grown%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20diners%20increasingly%20expect%20more%20spice%20in%20their%20foods.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESpice%20experts%20say%20the%20obsession%20may%20be%20shifting%20%E2%80%94%20and%20our%20taste%20buds%20will%20thank%20us.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20Friday%20at%20Doherty%20Memorial%20High%20School%20in%20Worcester%2C%20Massachusetts%2C%2014-year-old%20Harris%20Wolobah%20was%20handed%20a%20small%20coffin-shaped%20box%2C%20emblazoned%20with%20a%20skull%20and%20snake%2C%20that%20contains%20a%20single%20spicy%20tortilla%20chip%20called%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fextra-spicy-one-chip-challenge-tortilla-chip-pulled-teen-death-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOne%20Chip%20Challenge.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaqui%2C%20a%20Hershey%20company-owned%20brand%20that%20makes%20the%20chip%2C%20doesn't%20have%20a%20measurement%20for%20how%20spicy%20its%20product%20is%20or%20a%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EScoville%20Heat%20Unit%20(SHU)%20rating%20that%20shows%20the%20level%20of%20pungency%20of%20a%20pepper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20chip%20is%20made%20with%20the%20Carolina%20Reaper%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fred-dog-saloon-chicken-wings-naga-chilli-viper-challenge-hoxton-spice-scoville-2017-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENaga%20Viper%3C%2Fa%3E%20peppers%2C%20which%20are%20rated%20at%20about%201.6%20million%20and%201.4%20million%20SHU%2C%20respectively.%20Jalapeno%20peppers%2C%20in%20comparison%2C%20range%20from%202%2C500%20to%208%2C000%20SHU.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bchallenge%26quot%3B%20is%20simple%3A%20Eat%20the%20whole%20chip%20in%20one%20sitting%2C%20and%20see%20how%20long%20you%20can%20last%20without%20desperately%20grabbing%20a%20glass%20of%20milk%20or%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHealth%20experts%20have%20already%20warned%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteens-death-one-chip-challenge-spicy-food-safety-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20potential%20side%20effects%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20participating%20in%20the%20One%20Chip%20Challenge%3A%20vomiting%2C%20stomach%20pain%2C%20difficulty%20breathing%2C%20and%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.northeastern.edu%2F2023%2F09%2F07%2Fone-chip-challenge-dangerous%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecardiac%20arrest%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20Wolobah%2C%20like%20so%20many%20others%2C%20most%20likely%20either%20had%20no%20clue%20about%20the%20warnings%20or%20brushed%20it%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20countless%20others%20have%20already%20tried%20the%20challenge%20and%20shared%20their%20experience%20on%20YouTube.%20Pain%20quickly%20ensues%20but%20the%20participants%20seemed%20to%20come%20out%20of%20it%20okay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Wolobah%20ate%20the%20chip%2C%20the%20sophomore%20must%20have%20had%20an%20especially%20adverse%20reaction.%20According%20to%20Harris's%20mother%2C%20Lois%20Wolobah%2C%20he%20fainted%20and%20was%20sent%20to%20the%20nurse's%20office%20that%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20went%20there%2C%20he%20was%20lying%20down%20and%20I%20said%2C%20'What%20was%20the%20chip%20you%20ate%3F'%26quot%3B%20his%20mother%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fboston%2Fnews%2Fone-chip-challenge-death-paqui-harris-wolobah-worcester-massachusetts%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWBZ%20TV.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Wolobah%20showed%20his%20mom%20the%20Paqui%20brand%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fcarolina-reaper-madness-chip-spiciest-tortilla-one-challenge-2016-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOne%20Chip%20Challenge%3C%2Fa%3E.%20His%20father%2C%20Amos%2C%20said%20his%20son%20didn't%20have%20any%20pre-existing%20condition%2C%20at%20least%20to%20his%20knowledge%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWolobah%20died%20in%20his%20home%20hours%20later.%20Autopsy%20results%20have%20not%20yet%20been%20released%2C%20and%20the%20family%20and%20Hershey%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%20But%20the%20Wolobahs%20are%20pointing%20the%20blame%20squarely%20at%20the%20One%20Chip%20Challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaqui%20in%20response%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpaqui.com%2Fonechipchallenge%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it's%20working%20with%20retailers%20to%20%26quot%3Bremove%20the%20product%20from%20shelves.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20if%20the%20heat%20had%20anything%20to%20do%20with%20Wolobah's%20death%2C%20but%20the%20challenge's%20mere%20existence%20points%20to%20a%20uniquely%20American%20fascination%20with%20spice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fspiciest-dishes-us-2018-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erestaurants%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20sweat-inducing%20heat%20is%20almost%20expected%20on%20the%20menu.%20In%20the%20aisles%20of%20grocery%20stores%2C%20shoppers%20can%20choose%20from%20a%20dizzying%20selection%20of%20hot%20sauces.%20And%20in%20South%20Carolina%2C%20a%20farm%20is%20singlehandedly%20responsible%20for%20developing%20one%20of%20the%20hottest%20peppers%20ever%20eaten%20by%20mankind.%20The%20farm%20recently%20just%20topped%20its%20own%20record%20with%20a%20pepper%20rated%20at%20more%20than%202%20million%20Scoville%20Heat%20Units.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20demand%20has%20sometimes%20veered%20into%20the%20realm%20of%20morbid%20curiosity.%20Online%2C%20content%20creators%20farm%20for%20attention%20by%20taking%20part%20in%20extreme%20food%20challenges%2C%20expecting%20the%20pain%2C%20while%20millions%20watch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20we%20got%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt%20all%20began%20with%20an%20Italian%20explorer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20very%20brief%20summary%20of%20the%20chile%20peppers'%20origin%20starts%20somewhere%20in%20South%20America%20around%20Bolivia%20and%20Brazil%2C%20according%20to%20Stephanie%20Walker%2C%20an%20extension%20vegetable%20specialist%20at%20New%20Mexico%20State%20University's%20Chile%20Pepper%20Institute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20humans%20discovered%20peppers%20and%20their%20kick%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sensation%2C%20not%20a%20flavor%20%E2%80%94%20thousands%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20they%20immediately%20latched%20onto%20the%20fruit%20as%20a%20medicinal%20crop%2C%20and%20through%20human%20selection%2C%20a%20variety%20of%20chile%20peppers%20of%20different%20sizes%20and%20shapes%20started%20to%20appear%2C%20Walker%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20chile%20pepper's%20global%20proliferation%20began%20with%20a%20familiar%20name%3A%20Christopher%20Columbus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColumbus%20was%20looking%20for%20black%20peppercorns%20%E2%80%94%20a%20highly%20sought-after%20fruit%20at%20the%20time%20%E2%80%94%20but%20instead%20encountered%20a%20red%20plant%20that%20had%20a%20similar%20pungency%2C%20according%20to%20Walker.%20Hence%20the%20reason%20why%20we%20call%20the%20red%20fruit%2C%20chile%20%3Cem%3Epeppers%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20despite%20having%20no%20relationship%20to%20the%20black%20peppercorn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20Italian%20explorer%20took%20the%20seed%20back%20to%20the%20Old%20World%2C%20the%20fruit%20took%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20countries%2C%20especially%20Asian%20countries%2C%20African%20countries%2C%20really%20embraced%20it%20and%20started%20developing%20their%20own%20particular%20types%20of%20chile%20based%20on%20the%20flavors%2C%20the%20heat%20level%2C%20and%20other%20attributes%20that%20they%20preferred%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20professor%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20since%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20the%20US%20has%20consistently%20seen%20a%20steady%20increase%20in%20chile%20pepper%20demand%2C%20especially%20as%20immigration%20opened%20up%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%201980%20and%202020%2C%20chile%20pepper%20consumption%20increased%20more%20than%20twofold%2C%20from%20three%20pounds%20to%20seven%20pounds%20per%20person%20according%20to%20a%202021%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eresearch%20paper%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdpi.com%2F2073-4395%2F11%2F10%2F2040%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20Mexico%20State%20University's%20Department%20of%20Agricultural%20Economics%20and%20Agricultural%20Business%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConsumption%20of%20peppers%20is%20going%20up%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20it%20has%20been%20steadily%20for%20some%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Walker%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202020%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdownloads.usda.library.cornell.edu%2Fusda-esmis%2Ffiles%2F02870v86p%2Fj6731x86f%2F9306tr664%2Fvegean21.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20USDA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20chile%20pepper%20market%20was%20valued%20at%20%24100%20million.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20world%20record%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEd%20Currie%20%E2%80%94%20arguably%20the%20godfather%20of%20extremely%20hot%20chile%20peppers%20for%20his%20hand%20in%20developing%20the%20world's%20hottest%20chiles%20%E2%80%94%20traces%20his%20fascination%20with%20spice%20back%20to%20his%20college%20days%20in%20the%20'80s%20when%20his%20parents%20had%20to%20give%20him%20a%20reality%20check.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20parents%20told%20me%20I%20was%20going%20to%20die%20of%20heart%20disease%20or%20cancer%2C%20and%20I%20had%20better%20do%20something%20about%20it%20if%20I%20wanted%20to%20keep%20on%20living%20the%20lifestyle%20that%20I%20was%20leading%2C%26quot%3B%20Currie%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Currie%2C%20at%20that%20time%2C%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bfull-blown%20alcoholic%20and%20addict.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20habits%20didn't%20come%20to%20a%20sudden%20halt%2C%20but%20he%20did%20discover%20his%20interest%20in%20peppers%20during%20visits%20to%20the%20school%20library%20at%20absurd%20hours.%20In%20particular%2C%20Currie%20was%20piqued%20by%20the%20chile%20peppers'%20medicinal%20qualities.%20Perhaps%2C%20he%20thought%2C%20they%20contained%20the%20key%20to%20keep%20him%20chugging%20along.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20found%20out%20that%20the%20lowest%20indices%20of%20cancer%20and%20heart%20disease%20were%20around%20the%20equator%20from%20the%20two%20tropics%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurrie%20began%20sending%20letters%20all%20over%20the%20world%2C%20mostly%20to%20embassies%2C%20requesting%20samples%20of%20chiles%20or%20chile%20seeds.%20The%20internet%20still%20had%20a%20few%20years%20before%20it%20truly%20took%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20brief%20stint%20as%20a%20bank%20trust%20officer%20and%20a%20move%20to%20South%20Carolina%2C%20Currie%20opened%20a%20small%20booth%20at%20a%20flea%20market%20slinging%20homemade%20salsa%20using%20peppers%20he%20grew%20in%20his%20yard.%20In%202003%2C%20Puckerbutt%20Pepper%20Company%20was%20born.%20Currie%20by%20then%20also%20was%20a%20recovering%20addict%20for%20several%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225794%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ed%20Currie%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655eb8979c7d23cb3b9f20c3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224345%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEd%20Currie%20holds%20his%20Guinness%20Book%20of%20World%20Records%20certification%20for%20his%20new%20Pepper%20X.%3Cp%3EJeffrey%20Collins%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20at%20his%20farm%20in%20Fort%20Mills%2C%20where%20Currie%20developed%20two%20of%20the%20hottest%20peppers%20in%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20according%20to%20Guinness%20World%20Records.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20he%20set%20a%20world%20record%20with%20his%20Carolina%20Reaper%20pepper%2C%20which%20was%20recorded%20then%20with%20an%20average%20of%201.6%20million%20Scoville%20Heat%20Units%20%E2%80%94%20just%20about%20the%20same%20pungency%20as%20police%20pepper%20spray%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Associated%20Press.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20October%2C%20he%20broke%20his%20own%20record%20again%20after%20patiently%20waiting%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20for%20someone%20to%20dethrone%20his%20Reaper.%20The%20pepper%2C%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhot-ones-challenge-sauces-what-its-actually-like-review-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPepper%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20measures%20at%20about%202.7%20million%20SHU.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20South%20Carolina%20farmer%20gave%20three%20reasons%20why%20he%20and%20his%20team%20created%20peppers%20that%20are%20essentially%20suitable%20for%20torture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%2C%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20we%20can%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%2C%20Currie's%20interest%20in%20the%20chile%20pepper's%20medicinal%20qualities%20persists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20three%2C%20%26quot%3Bfor%20flavor%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurrie%20doesn't%20enjoy%20burning%20himself%20up%20more%20than%20anyone%20else%2C%20although%20he's%20likely%20developed%20an%20extraordinary%20tolerance%20over%20the%20years%20testing%20hot%20peppers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20challenges%20that%20are%20spawned%20from%20his%20product%2C%20including%20the%20One%20Chip%20Challenge%20that%20so%20happens%20to%20be%20seasoned%20with%20the%20Reaper%2C%20might%20make%20for%20effective%20marketing%2C%20but%20Currie%20doesn't%20care%20to%20participate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20do%20those%20challenges%20'cause%20they're%20stupid%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20developing%20a%20hotter%20pepper%20is%20part%20of%20a%20business%20model%20that%20would%20allow%20him%20to%20sell%2C%20for%20example%2C%20a%20hotter%20sauce%20with%20less%20pepper%20he%20says%2C%20but%20also%2C%20believe%20it%20or%20not%2C%20about%20creating%20a%20better-tasting%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20philosophy%20for%20me%20is%20how%20can%20I%20take%20something%20that's%20already%20popular%20and%20make%20it%20taste%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMake%20it%20hotter%2C%20chef%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20as%20long%20as%20Roberto%20Santiba%C3%B1ez%20was%20based%20in%20the%20US%2C%20the%20chef%20of%20almost%20four%20decades%20recalls%20Americans%20having%20a%20unique%20affinity%20to%20spicy%20foods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESantiba%C3%B1ez%2C%20a%20Mexico%20City%20native%20who%20opened%20three%20restaurants%20in%20his%20hometown%2C%20moved%20to%20New%20York%20City%20in%201996%2C%20where%20he%20would%20later%20open%20Fonda%20in%202009%20serving%20contemporary%20Mexican%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20his%20family%20got%20a%20taste%20of%20his%20spin%20on%20his%20native%20cuisine%2C%20they%20were%20shocked%20by%20the%20levels%20of%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Mexico%20and%20in%20school%20at%20Le%20Cordon%20Bleu%20in%20Paris%2C%20Santiba%C5%84ez%20felt%20that%20restaurants%20and%20chefs%20cooked%20with%20spice%20but%20with%20a%20bit%20of%20caution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20however%2C%20Santiba%C5%84ez%20has%20to%20remember%3A%20%26quot%3BPeople%20really%20go%20for%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20what%20I've%20experienced%20is%20if%20you%20promise%20people%20with%20wordings%20like%2C%20'This%20is%20a%20spicy%20sauce%2C'%20then%20people%20really%20want%20it%20spicy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20not%20fail%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Fonda%20patrons%20ask%20for%20more%20heat%20on%20top%20of%20the%20hot%20salsas%20already%20served%20at%20his%20restaurant%2C%20Santiba%C3%B1ez%20said%2C%20and%20he'll%20oblige%20by%20giving%20them%20diced%20habanero%2C%20a%20pepper%20rated%20at%20150%2C000%20to%20350%2C000%20SHU.%20In%20his%20cookbooks%2C%20the%20chef%20will%20advise%20home%20cooks%20not%20to%20be%20afraid%20to%20add%20more%20spice%2C%20understanding%20what%20his%20audience%20expects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans'%20high%20tolerance%20for%20spice%20at%20restaurants%20can%20also%20be%20charted%20with%20the%20explosion%20of%20the%20Nashville%20Hot%20Chicken%20scene.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dish%20%E2%80%94%20generally%2C%20fried%20chicken%20slathered%20with%20a%20cayenne-pepper-based%20sauce%20or%20paste%20and%20typically%20served%20with%20pickles%20and%20white%20bread%20%E2%80%94%20has%20been%20around%20for%20several%20decades%2C%20perhaps%20even%20as%20far%20back%20as%20the%201930s%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Fsections%2Fthesalt%2F2016%2F04%2F28%2F471436355%2Fhow-a-cheating-husband-gave-rise-to-nashvilles-hot-chicken-craze%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENPR%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrince's%20Hot%20Chicken%20Shack%20in%20Nashville%20is%20often%20cited%20as%20the%20originator.%20The%20lore%20behind%20the%20recipe%20is%20said%20to%20have%20involved%20a%20woman%20creating%20the%20dish%20to%20punish%20her%20cheating%20partner%2C%20Thornton%20Prince%2C%20the%20great-uncle%20of%20the%20restaurant's%20owner%2C%20Andre%20Prince.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20however%2C%20the%20hot%20chicken%20appears%20to%20have%20received%20renewed%20attention%20with%20headlines%20on%20how%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbc.ca%2Fradio%2Fcostofliving%2Fwhy-did-you-cross-the-road-to-get-a-hot-chicken-sandwich-along-with-everyone-else-1.6156397%2Fwhy-the-appetite-for-chicken-sandwiches-is-red-hot-and-shows-no-signs-of-slowing-down-1.6156652%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENashville%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fsocal%2Fdaily-pilot%2Fentertainment%2Fstory%2F2021-01-06%2Famong-all-else-2020-was-the-year-of-nashville-hot-chicken-sandwiches%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHot%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wattagnet.com%2Fpoultry-future%2Farticle%2F15531864%2Fis-nashville-hot-chicken-the-next-big-menu-trend-wattagnet%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChicken%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbittersoutherner.com%2Fhow-hot-chicken-really-happened%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexploding%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fchelseadavis%2F2023%2F02%2F24%2Foaklands-world-famous-hotboys-sells-1000000-nashville-hot-chicken-sandwiches-since-their-2019-opening%2F%3Fsh%3D59684a6e2927%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epopularity%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F0pY1SzwHwfQ%3Fsi%3DToNZvdkGrF6A_kWq%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20man%20responsible%20for%20the%20hot%20chicken's%20prominence%20in%20southern%20California%20is%20Johnny%20Ray%20Zone%2C%20a%20Los%20Angeles%20native%20with%20a%20childhood%20love%20for%20spicy%20food%20and%20snacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20a%20big%20fan%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Ftrue-story-flamin-hot-cheetos-richard-montanez-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHot%20Cheetos%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20even%20though%20they're%20not%20spicy%2C%26quot%3B%20Zone%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BI%20ate%20so%20many%20of%20those%20I%20had%20to%20get%20my%20appendix%20cut%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20his%20father's%20untimely%20death%2C%20Zone%2C%20who%20by%20now%20had%20worked%20his%20way%20up%20from%20dishwasher%20to%20executive%20chef%2C%20took%20a%20trip%20to%20Nashville%20and%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20the%20iconic%20hot%20chicken%20dish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELA%20needed%20this%2C%20Zone%20thought.%20In%202014%2C%20he%20started%20Howlin'%20Rays%20out%20of%20a%20food%20truck%2C%20serving%20Nashville%20hot%20chicken%20quarters%20with%20side%20dishes%20such%20as%20braised%20collard%20greens%20and%20a%20mac%20and%20cheese%20salad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20simple%20genius%20behind%20Howlin'%20Rays%20and%20its%20eventual%20%26quot%3Bviral%20success%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fsocal%2Fdaily-pilot%2Fentertainment%2Fstory%2F2021-01-06%2Famong-all-else-2020-was-the-year-of-nashville-hot-chicken-sandwiches%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Los%20Angeles%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20described%2C%20was%20putting%20the%20hot%20chicken%20in%20sandwich%20form%20%E2%80%94%20something%20Nashville%20did%20not%20have%20at%20the%20time%2C%20according%20to%20Zone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20we%20did%20that%2C%20then%20it%20took%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224910%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20guys%20preparing%20Nashville%20Hote%20Chicken%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655eb9dc9c7d23cb3b9f2113%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChef%20Johnny%20Ray%20Zone%2C%20left%2C%20prepares%20Nashville%20Hot%20Chicken%20at%20LA%20Food%20Fests%202016.%3Cp%3ETara%20Ziemba%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20one%20part%20of%20the%20Nashville%20Hot%20Chicken%20experience%20Zone%20made%20sure%20to%20preserve%20was%20offering%20different%20levels%20of%20spice%2C%20going%20from%20mild%20all%20the%20way%20up%20to%20%26quot%3Bhowlin'%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bhowlin'%20plus%20plus%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20off-menu.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Nashville%2C%20every%20hot%20chicken%20restaurant%20offers%20different%20levels%20of%20spice%20and%20might%20have%20a%20unique%20name%20for%20each%20level%2C%20Zone%20said.%20And%20each%20restaurant%20had%20its%20own%20take%20on%20what%20their%20level%20of%20%26quot%3Bhot%26quot%3B%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20part%20of%20the%20lure%20of%20hot%20chicken%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20hoards%20of%20customers%20are%20coming%20in%20requesting%20the%20top%20three%20spice%20levels%20available.%20Zone%20said%20that%20they're%20actually%20%26quot%3Bnot%20that%20popular.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20first-time%20customers%20do%20feel%20adventurous%2C%20Zone%20makes%20sure%20to%20give%20them%20a%20small%20sample%20of%20what%20to%20expect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20people%20hear%20so%20much%20stuff%20about%20us%2C%20and%20it's%20their%20first%20time%20trying%20it%2C%20we%20don't%20want%20their%20experience%20to%20be%20ruined%2C%26quot%3B%20Zone%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20keep%20it%20authentic%20for%20how%20hot%20it%20is%20in%20Nashville.%20We%20don't%20want%20to%20dumb%20it%20down%20just%20for%20sales.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20nuanced%20heat%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENovelty%20chip%20challenges%2C%20extreme%20peppers%2C%20and%20hot%20chicken%20satisfy%20the%20appetite%20of%20a%20small%20base%20of%20thrill%20seekers%20%E2%80%94%20while%20millions%20of%20others%20just%20watch%20%E2%80%94%20but%20our%20dishes%20aren't%20necessarily%20getting%20hotter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20pendulum%20could%20be%20swinging%20the%20other%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDenise%20Purcell%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20content%20and%20education%20of%20Specialty%20Food%20Association%2C%20which%20highlights%20trends%20in%20global%2C%20artisanal%20foods%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20more%20and%20more%20food%20retailers%20and%20purveyors%20are%20thinking%20about%20how%20to%20incorporate%20heat%20to%20complement%20the%20foods%20we%20eat%20rather%20than%20overpowering%20our%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20trend%20seemed%20to%20be%20the%20hotter%2C%20the%20better%C2%A0%E2%80%94%20like%20ghost%20pepper%20and%20whatever%20the%20hottest%20pepper%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20Purcell%20said.%20%26quot%3BLet's%20see%20if%20people%20could%20handle%20it.%20And%20that%20is%20giving%20way%20a%20little%20bit%20to%20this%20more%20nuanced%20heat%20idea%2C%20where%20it's%20not%20just%20all%20about%20burning%20your%20tongue%20and%20seeing%20what%20your%20tolerance%20is.%20It's%20heat%20that%20enhances%20the%20flavor.%20It's%20things%20like%20hot%20honey%20we%20see%20now%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20menus%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20packaged%20products.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20push%20to%20incorporate%20a%20more%20nuanced%20heat%20is%20also%20being%20commercialized%2C%20as%20fast%20food%20companies%20roll%20out%20sweet%20and%20spicy%20products%20or%20sauces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fpopeyes-fried-chicken-review-2017-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPopeyes%20Louisiana%20Kitchen%3C%2Fa%3E%20intermittently%20brings%20back%20its%20hot%20honey%20sauce%20and%20chicken.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsurprising-facts-mcdonalds-hamburgers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcDonald's%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20month%20released%20its%20Sweet%20%26amp%3B%20Spicy%20Jam%20sauce%20for%20a%20limited%20time%2C%20which%20incorporates%20Szechuan%20peppercorn%20and%20cayenne%20pepper%2C%20according%20to%20the%20fast%20food%20restaurant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Zone%2C%20the%20spicy%20foods%20he's%20intimately%20familiar%20with%20are%20dishes%20from%20one%20of%20many%20Thai%20restaurants%20that%20dot%20Los%20Angeles%20and%20have%20incorporated%20a%20balance%20of%20sweet%20and%20spicy%20like%20larb%20or%20yum%20nua.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20all%20these%20different%20Thai%20classics%2C%20the%20sugar%20balances%20out%20the%20spice%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20how%20long%20have%20they%20been%20serving%20that%3F%20Hundreds%20